The paper deals with a problem of sampling a Wiener process and transmitting it over a channel with queueing and random delay, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the optimal sampling strategy for minimizing the mean square estimation error, which involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and optimization (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions recent research on Age-of-Information, which is a topic in networking and information systems (cs.NI).
